      <h1>Bakery Equipment Suppliers in India: City-by-City Dealer Directory 2026</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span>📅 Updated: March 2026</span>
        <span>⏱️ 15 min read</span>
        <span>🇮🇳 All major cities covered</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Finding the right bakery equipment supplier in India is one of the most important decisions you'll make when setting up or upgrading your bakery.</strong> Buy from the wrong dealer and you risk overpaying by 20–30%, receiving grey-market imports with no warranty, or being stuck without spare parts when your oven breaks down mid-season. This guide covers every major city's equipment market, what to ask dealers, how to negotiate on price, and the red flags that should make you walk away.</p>

    <p>India's commercial bakery equipment market is worth over ₹2,500 crore annually and is growing at roughly 12% per year, driven by the rapid expansion of bakery chains, cloud kitchens, and artisan bakeries. That growth has attracted hundreds of equipment dealers — ranging from excellent authorised importers to dodgy traders selling refurbished Chinese imports as "new" equipment. Knowing how to navigate this market is a real skill.</p>

