    <h2>1. Delhi & NCR: India's Biggest Bakery Equipment Hub</h2>
    <p>Delhi is undoubtedly the largest and most competitive bakery equipment market in India. The sheer density of dealers means prices are lower and selection is wider than almost anywhere else. If you're buying serious commercial equipment and can travel, Delhi is worth the trip.</p>

    <h3>Kirti Nagar: The Industrial Equipment Heartland</h3>
    <p>Kirti Nagar in West Delhi is primarily known as India's furniture market, but it also has a significant cluster of commercial kitchen and bakery equipment dealers tucked in among the furniture showrooms. The area running from the Kirti Nagar metro station towards Shivaji Park Road has over a dozen dealers specialising in commercial bakery, restaurant, and hotel kitchen equipment.</p>
    <p>What you'll find in Kirti Nagar: deck ovens, rotary rack ovens, commercial mixers (both Indian and imported), proofing chambers, sheeting machines, dough dividers, bread slicers, and display cases. Dealers here tend to stock mid-to-high-end equipment and are more accustomed to dealing with commercial buyers than home bakers.</p>
    <p>Typical approach: most Kirti Nagar dealers don't display fixed prices. You'll be shown equipment, given a verbal quote, and expected to negotiate. Don't accept the first price — counter-offering 15–20% below the asking price is standard practice. See the negotiation section below for tactics.</p>

    <h3>Karol Bagh: More Accessible, More Entry-Level</h3>
    <p>Karol Bagh's equipment dealers are concentrated on and around Pusa Road and the adjoining lanes near the Karol Bagh metro station. The market here has a broader range — from entry-level equipment for small bakeries and cafés to mid-range commercial gear. You're more likely to find countertop ovens, small mixers, and food processors here alongside larger commercial equipment.</p>
    <p>Karol Bagh dealers are more used to selling to small business owners and first-time buyers. They're often willing to explain equipment in more detail and provide installation support. Prices are sometimes a little higher than Kirti Nagar for comparable equipment, but the buying experience is often smoother.</p>

    <h3>Wazirpur Industrial Area: Factory-Direct Pricing</h3>
    <p>Wazirpur, in North Delhi, is an industrial area with several manufacturers and distributors of commercial kitchen equipment. Buying here can save 10–15% compared to retail dealers because you're closer to the source. It's less visitor-friendly — this is where trade buyers go, not walk-in shoppers. Call ahead and know what you want before visiting.</p>

    <h3>Lawrence Road & Tri Nagar: Budget Equipment</h3>
    <p>For budget equipment, second-hand machinery, and Indian-manufactured gear, Lawrence Road and Tri Nagar in West Delhi have a cluster of dealers. Prices are lower, but quality is more variable. Good for spare parts, accessories, and second-hand equipment if you know what you're looking for.</p>

