    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which city in India has the cheapest bakery equipment? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Delhi has the largest and most competitive bakery equipment market in India, with prices typically 5–15% lower than other major cities for comparable equipment. Within Delhi, Kirti Nagar and Wazirpur industrial area offer the most competitive prices. Kolkata is competitive for budget and mid-range Indian-made equipment. However, once you factor in freight costs for delivery from Delhi to your city, the price advantage may narrow for smaller purchases.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I buy bakery equipment online in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, platforms like IndiaMart, Amazon India, and Flipkart have bakery equipment. However, for commercial equipment above ₹30,000, physical dealers in competitive markets offer better prices and more importantly, include installation, warranty support, and after-sales service. Use online platforms for price research and small accessory purchases. For major commercial equipment, buy from a verified physical dealer.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How do I verify a bakery equipment dealer is genuine in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Five key steps: (1) Verify their GST number on gst.gov.in — it should match their name and address. (2) Contact the brand manufacturer or Indian distributor directly to confirm dealer authorisation. (3) Check Google Business reviews for consistent history over multiple years. (4) Ask for 2–3 customer references and actually call them. (5) Visit their physical showroom/office before making payment. Legitimate dealers welcome all of these checks.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How much discount can I expect when buying bakery equipment in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For a single piece of equipment, negotiating 5–12% off the asking price is typically achievable with research and patience. For a bundle purchase (full bakery setup worth ₹5 lakh or more), discounts of 10–18% are common if you get competing quotes from multiple dealers. Cash payment (immediate bank transfer) often unlocks an additional 3–5% discount. Timing your purchase at end of quarter or after major holidays also helps.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is it safe to buy second-hand bakery equipment in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, with proper inspection and from a reputable source. Second-hand commercial bakery equipment in good condition typically costs 40–60% of the new price and can be excellent value, especially for ovens, mixers, and refrigeration. Key checks: verify the age and service history, test the equipment thoroughly before paying, have a technician inspect heating elements and electrical systems, and confirm spare parts are available for that model. See our full <a href="/blog/used-bakery-equipment-guide">Used Bakery Equipment Guide</a> for a complete inspection checklist.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What bakery equipment markets are in Delhi? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Delhi's main bakery equipment markets are: Kirti Nagar (West Delhi) for commercial-grade ovens, mixers, and professional equipment; Karol Bagh (Central Delhi) for a wider range including entry-level equipment; Wazirpur Industrial Area (North Delhi) for factory-direct and distributor pricing; and Lawrence Road / Tri Nagar for budget equipment and second-hand machinery. Kirti Nagar is the best starting point for serious commercial equipment buyers.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

